{
  "stem": "8.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Again, this is because it was the month of the Jewish Elul, and that this is when we used to blow the shofar every day.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that was the sign that there will be a redemption.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Somehow I always talked myself into some kind of a hope.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There was an incident that we walked one day and I found a little knife-- maybe a child's toy knife-- and a-- and a necklace with a Magen David on it, a gold necklace.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I was so excited and happy on it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And because my dress was somewhat more open, I put it on my mother's neck to wear it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And one day, the lageralteste, or the blockalteste, saw it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "She was a Jewish woman.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "She was very, very cruel.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And she yanked it off her neck.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And my mother became inflamed, and she took the courage to yell at this woman.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And she said shame on you, you take away one little thing that my daughter has.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Now for that you must reward her.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "My mother demanded that they must reward me with something.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And so I got an extra ladle of, of, of food from this blockalteste who somehow was stunned by mother's-- by my mother's courage.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "My mother told her, shame on you, you Jewish girl, how you treat a little child like that.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "My, my aunt, who was kind of a [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "She was young, a few years older.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "She went to the-- to the latrines.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "The latrines were the place where we usually exchanged news, and that was just one of the barracks with about 100 holes on a-- on a platform.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And the holes were large enough so that my aunt one night-- because she had dysentery-- she fell into the latrine.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
